  "prompt": "Is a passport compulsory to travel on flights within India?",
  "response": "No, a passport is not compulsory for domestic flights within India. For domestic travel, you can use government-issued photo identification such as:\n\n- Voter ID\n- Aadhar Card\n- Driving License\n- PAN Card\n\nHowever, you will need a valid passport for international travel. Always check with your airline for their specific identification requirements before you travel.",
